      "position": 4,
      "description": "<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://instructure-uploads-pdx.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/account_152790000000000001/attachments/19401206/dp_app.css\"><div class=\"description user_content teacher-version enhanced\" data-resource-type=\"assignment.body\" data-resource-id=\"1375500\">\n<div class=\"description user_content teacher-version enhanced\" data-resource-type=\"assignment.body\" data-resource-id=\"637323\">\n<div class=\"description user_content teacher-version enhanced\">\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Week 4 Homework:</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Make sure you review the <strong><em>Homework Submission Protocol</em></strong> section of the syllabus before turning in your homework.</li>\n<li>Upload a single <em><strong>R script file</strong></em> with the code for all of <strong>Week 4 </strong>homework. But before you upload it, change the extension to <em><strong>.txt</strong></em> so that the grader can view the file within the Canvas grading environment.</li>\n<li>Name your file something akin to <em><strong>HW04MurphyJ.txt </strong></em>to indicate the homework number and your name.</li>\n<li>Your file should have a header indicating your name and perhaps a partner's. See syllabus.</li>\n<li>I hope you found this homework to be good practice for this week's topics!</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><script src=\"https://instructure-uploads-pdx.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/account_152790000000000001/attachments/19401205/dp_app.js\"></script>",
