      "id": 1438699,
      "position": 5,
      "description": "<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://instructure-uploads-pdx.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/account_152790000000000001/attachments/19401206/dp_app.css\"><h2>Purpose</h2>\n<p><em>The purpose of this exercise is to help you engage with the reading and prepare for in-class discussion. It also helps you to find key points and seek clarifications as needed.</em></p>\n<h2>Tasks</h2>\n<p><span><strong>1:&nbsp;</strong><strong>Choose two quotes: </strong>Choose <strong>one quote from materials due Monday</strong> and choose <strong>one quote from the material due Tuesday</strong>. Write your name, the quote, and a parenthetical reference (or chapter number if applicable) in your entry or \"reply\".&nbsp; &nbsp;(Students will often be asked to read their quotes and explain why you chose them in zoom class sessions.)</span></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Students may choose a quote because they have questions about it, they want to talk more about the subject, they thought it was critical to the reading, or it reminded them of other ideas or readings from the course. Students should think about how the quote relates to the overall argument or theme of the piece and how it relates to other readings and ideas covered in the course. Students should also critically engage with the chosen quote, to be able to explain what they especially like about it or dislike about it.</p>\n<p><span><strong>Reminder</strong>: Parenthetical reference is last name of author(s) and then page number. For example, (Birke 372). For electronic sources without page numbers, indicate author(s) and chapter number. For example, (Roughgarden Ch 8)</span></p>\n<p><span><strong>To begin your initial post, use the Reply button at the bottom of this page.&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<h2>Time Frame</h2>\n<p>Post by <strong>noon on Tuesday</strong>.</p>\n<h2>Criteria for Success</h2>\n<p><span>Grading:</span><strong><span>&nbsp;</span>3 points</strong><span>&nbsp;</span><span>for posting a quote.&nbsp; This will be graded&nbsp;</span><strong>credit/no credit</strong><span>.</span></p><script src=\"https://instructure-uploads-pdx.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/account_152790000000000001/attachments/19401205/dp_app.js\"></script>",
