      "description": "<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://instructure-uploads-pdx.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/account_152790000000000001/attachments/19401206/dp_app.css\"><header class=\"discussion-section clearfix\"></header>\n<h2 id=\"JDL3JNT7C823UIV4IRH5\"><span>Purpose</span></h2>\n<p><em>The weekly Discussion Forum allows students to assess the week's material, share some of what they learned in the weekly activity, and communicate and collaborate in this process with others in the class through the interactive discussion.</em></p>\n<h2><span>Tasks</span></h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<ol>\n<li>After reading, watching, and listening to the required materials and completing the reflection activity, <strong>post to this forum</strong>. To receive credit, your post must include the following:\n<ol>\n<li>What are the <strong>two most important takeaways </strong>from this week's required material?<strong> (</strong>That is, what are the most important points from the week's required material for our work in WGQS/ES 350 class?)</li>\n<li>Share <strong>which reflection activity</strong> you chose and <strong>something you learned</strong> from the<em> Reflection Activity</em> (you control how much detail you share with your peers and the instructor from the activity)</li>\n<li>Your post must include <strong>at least one direct quote</strong> <strong>and cite at least one source</strong> from the week's required materials.\n<ul>\n<li>When you quote from course materials, please include parenthetical citations (for instance, with the author\u2019s last name and page number of the citation).&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Be sure to explain why you think the quote was important or connect it to your takeaways.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Reply to a post that has no more than one other existing reply (until all posts have at least one reply)</strong>.&nbsp;\n<ul>\n<li><strong>First, </strong>identify something that they stated or cited that you thought was insightful and explain why OR identify something in particular that you thought was related to your own analysis and explain why.</li>\n<li><strong>Second, </strong>building on their post, what is something that might be further explored? How is it related to their post?&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"JDL3JNT7C823UIV4IRH5\">How to Post</h2>\n<p><span><strong><span style=\"background-color: #fbeeb8;\">To begin your initial post, use the Reply button at the bottom of this page</span>. Create a descriptive Subject line</strong> related to your post content (e.g., something like: \"Assimilate in STEM fields (or perish)\"), and input your post text into the \"Message\" field.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span>You may choose to complete this in a word-processing program first so you can save your work. Then copy and paste into Canvas after it is edited. Use the formatting toolbar in Canvas as desired.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong>To create your replies</strong></span>: Click on the Discussion thread (indicated by the Subject line) for the reading response post to which you would like to reply. In the bottom right corner of the Message of the post, you will see a link for \"Reply\" (next to a link that reads \"Permalink\"). Click on \"Reply,\" and you will get a new \"Message\" box in which you can input your reply (feel free to use the formatting toolbar if you wish).</p>\n<h2 id=\"JDL3JNT7C823UIV4IRH5\">Time Frame</h2>\n<p><span>To complete this discussion, your initial posting is due by&nbsp;</span><strong>Friday, Feb 6 (end of the day)</strong><span>. The response is due by <strong>Saturday, Feb 7 (end of the day)</strong>. (You are always welcome and able to complete all the coursework for the week by Friday if you choose.)</span></p>\n<h2 id=\"JDL3JNT7C823UIV4IRH5\">Criteria for Success</h2>\n<p>Students who have completed ALL FOUR TASKS (in a post and response) will receive credit and students who have not completed ALL FOUR TASKS will not receive credit.&nbsp;</p><script src=\"https://instructure-uploads-pdx.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/account_152790000000000001/attachments/19401205/dp_app.js\"></script>",
